HEADWORD: Taproom
<hw>Tap"room`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A room where liquors
are kept on tap; a barroom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ambassador was put one night into a miserable
<qex>taproom</qex>, full of soldiers smoking.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Taproot</ent>⟦br⟧
